  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate", 
    "date": "2018-03-01T05:00:00Z", 
    "text": "End Taxpayer Subsidies for Drug Ads Act\n\nThis bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to prohibit tax deductions for expenses relating to direct-to-consumer advertising of prescription drugs.\n\n\"Direct-to-consumer advertising\" is any dissemination, by or on behalf of a sponsor of a prescription drug product, of an advertisement that is: (1) in regard to the drug product, and (2) primarily targeted to the general public."
  }, 
